properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 5:48AM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTER WEATHER WILL IMPACT TRAVEL THIS WEEKEND...

.Another round of snow will arrive late this afternoon and early
evening, bringing snowfall totals of 2 to 6 inches, heaviest
along the lakeshore. Along with the snowfall, considerable
blowing and drifting snow will occur, especially from the Fox
Valley to the lakeshore counties. The worst conditions will occur
along the lakeshore areas, where the highest snowfall totals are
expected, and northeast winds will gust to 35 to 40 mph. Travel
conditions will be significantly impacted.

The strong northeast winds will also result in increased
potential for lakeshore flooding, shoreline erosion, and ice
shoves on the bay and Lake Winnebago.

* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow expected. Total snow accumulations
of up to two inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Brown and Winnebago Counties.

* WHEN...From 3 PM this afternoon to 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds could
bring down tree branches, resulting in localized power outages.
Ice shoves could occur along the Bay and along the south shore
of Lake Winnebago.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 6 AM CST SUNDAY
